      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that insists on interpreting the Constitution according to the understanding of the framers at the time it was written. The main legal justification for originalism is that it provides a stable and predictable legal framework, preventing judges from imposing their personal beliefs on the law. It also respects the democratic process, as the Constitution was ratified by the people and their representatives, not by judges. Originalists argue that this approach preserves the integrity of the Constitution and prevents judicial activism.",
